# Full Stack Estate Platform

A full-stack real estate application designed for modern, scalable deployment. It includes a robust API, a responsive frontend, and real-time communication capabilities.

---

## 🌟 Features

- User authentication and authorization
- Property listing and filtering
- Real-time notifications via WebSocket
- RESTful API with Prisma and PostgreSQL
- React-based frontend with Vite for fast development

---

## 🧰 Tech Stack

### Frontend
- Vite
- React (likely from `vite.config.js` and src structure)
- TailwindCSS (if applicable)
- Axios

### Backend
- Node.js
- Express.js
- Prisma ORM
- PostgreSQL (expected from Prisma)

### Real-Time
- WebSocket (socket.io or native ws in the `socket/` directory)

---

## 📁 Directory Structure
full-stack-estate-main/
├── api/ # Backend API with Express and Prisma
├── client/ # Frontend with Vite and React
└── socket/ # WebSocket server for real-time functionality


---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js (v16 or higher recommended)
- PostgreSQL (ensure a database is available for Prisma)
- pnpm or npm

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://your-repo-url/full-stack-estate-main.git
cd full-stack-estate-main

2. Backend Setup (API)
cd api
npm install
# Configure your database connection in prisma/schema.prisma
npx prisma generate
npx prisma migrate dev --name init
npm run dev

3. Frontend Setup (Client)
cd ../client
npm install
npm run dev

4. WebSocket Server Setup
cd ../socket
npm install
node app.js



